<TITLE> 'Dacoit leader' beaten to death in Magura </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Magura, Apr 15 (bdnews24.com)  An alleged leader of a dacoit gang was beaten to death by a mob in Char Batajor village in sadar upazila in Magura early on Thursday. Thirty-year old Faruk Hossain was the top dacoit leader of the country's south-western region, Magura sadar police chief A Raquib Khan said. Khan said the incident occurred when residents of the village came to know that Faruk arrived at the village to meet secretly his family members on Wednesday night. They beat him up severely and he died on his way to Magura sadar hospital, the police chief said. There are 10 cases, including six relating to dacoity, against Faruk in Magura, Jessore, Jhenaidah, Narail and Faridpur, the added. bd
